The
Steelers
,
whose
history
may
be
traced
to
a
regional
pro
team
that
was
established
in
the
early
1920s
,
joined
the
NFL
as
the
Pittsburgh
Pirates
on
July
8
,
1933.
The
team
was
owned
by
Art
Rooney
and
took
its
original
name
from
the
baseball
team
of
the
same
name
,
as
was
common
practice
for
NFL
teams
at
the
time
.
